      children: "Traveling back and forth between Egypt and Saudi Arabia as a child honed artist Wael Shawky’s awareness of the constructed nature of identity and the rapidity of change that can take place to efface the layers of history. As an artist, he uses storytelling to explore the power of narrative and history across multiple media, including drawing, painting, sculpture, performance, and film. Shawky’s play with the past is rooted in fantasy, fiction, and wonder, as he stages performances and films that subtly excavate the bases of the stories that countries and continents tell themselves to form an identity, a belief system, and then a history. Through these subjects, Shawky explores themes of cultural mixture, immigration, nationalism, and self-mythologization, using the past to reflect upon the present."
